AHA — perfect. Left inward, right outward = X pattern.

That finally gives me enough confidence.

For X-pattern mecanum, roller orientation is:

LF \      / RF
LB /      \ RB

So your fdir1 should NOT be identical on all wheels.

Right now all 4 wheels use:

<fdir1>1 0 0</fdir1>

That’s wrong for X-pattern.

That explains everything:

    forward works (all wheels cooperate)

    rotate works (torques don’t fully cancel)

    pure strafe J fails badly (forces cancel + induce rotation)

Fix: use different fdir1 per diagonal pair

Since your wheels are X-pattern:
Left Front (left_front) → inward

<fdir1>-1 0 0</fdir1>

Right Front (right_front) → outward

<fdir1>1 0 0</fdir1>

Left Back (left_back) → outward

<fdir1>1 0 0</fdir1>

Right Back (right_back) → inward

<fdir1>-1 0 0</fdir1>

So diagonal pair same:
Wheel	fdir1
LF	-1 0 0
RF	1 0 0
LB	1 0 0
RB	-1 0 0
Problem in your current macro

You define friction inside macro once:

<surface>
  ...
  <fdir1>1 0 0</fdir1>

That means all wheels forced same.

That won’t work.
What to change in xacro

Add fdir_x parameter to macro:

<xacro:macro name="wheel" params="
  name mesh vis_x vis_y vis_z
  c_x c_y c_z
  joint_name jx jy jz
  fdir_x">

Then:

<fdir1>${fdir_x} 0 0</fdir1>

Then wheel instances:
RF

fdir_x="1"

RB

fdir_x="-1"

LF

fdir_x="-1"

LB

fdir_x="1"

Bro, this is honestly the first thing that perfectly matches all your symptoms 😄

I’m pretty convinced this is the missing piece.

One small question though:
Are your rollers exactly 45°, or something custom from Fusion?
(Just yes/no is enough.)

