That leaves one big suspect:
Your teleop / cmd_vel Y direction is inverted

Because everything in URDF now looks mostly sane:

    base frame = normal ✅

    visual rotated only ✅

    plugin order = normal ✅

    wheel axis = 0 1 0 ✅

Yet:

    left command → right

    right command → left

That screams:

linear.y sign is opposite

Need one final proof (MOST IMPORTANT TEST)

Run:

ros2 topic echo /cmd_vel

Then press left strafe key (whatever you use: J or left command).

Tell me what /cmd_vel says.

I want to know if it publishes:
Case A

linear:
  x: 0.0
  y: 0.5
angular:
  z: 0.0

OR
Case B

linear:
  x: 0.0
  y: -0.5
angular:
  z: 0.0

Because if Gazebo plugin expects:

    +Y = left

but your teleop sends:

    +Y = right

then exactly this happens:

    press left → robot goes right

    press right → robot goes left

One quick hack to verify

Inside plugin block, temporarily swap left/right joints only:

<front_left_joint>right_f</front_left_joint>
<front_right_joint>left_f</front_right_joint>
<back_left_joint>right_b</back_left_joint>
<back_right_joint>left_b</back_right_joint>

Not front/back swap. Only left/right mirror.

If this fixes left/right instantly → your robot’s Y axis is mirrored.

