yes thn y is it ionverted now?

If you’re using teleop_twist_keyboard, then by default:

    +x = forward

    +y = left

    -y = right

So if pressing J (left strafe) makes robot go right, then one of only two things is true now:
1) Robot Y-axis is mirrored (MOST likely)

Even though base_footprint is not rotated anymore, your robot geometry may still effectively be mirrored in Y.

I noticed something suspicious in wheel placement:
Right wheels:

right_front  jy=" 0.102054"
right_back   jy=" 0.102054"

Left wheels:

left_front   jy="-0.102054"
left_back    jy="-0.102054"

According to ROS convention:

+Y = LEFT
-Y = RIGHT

But your model says:

right wheels -> +Y
left wheels  -> -Y

BROOOO.

That is reversed.

That means physically your robot is built like:

+Y side = right
-Y side = left

Gazebo plugin assumes opposite.

That alone would invert strafe.
This may be the actual root cause

Your wheel names say:

right_front
left_front

But coordinates say the opposite.
Quick proof

In your xacro:
This:

right_front jy=" 0.102054"

should probably be:

right_front jy="-0.102054"

And left:

left_front jy="0.102054"

2) Less likely: plugin uses opposite Y convention

Possible, but less likely.
