Bro — I found the issue. Not one, two major issues in this code.
Issue 1 (BIGGEST): Your wheel names and wheel positions are mirrored

Look at this carefully:
right_front visual

vis_y="-0.102054"

Visual says right wheel is at negative Y → correct (ROS convention)

But joint says:

jx="-0.083355"
jy=" 0.102054"

Joint says right wheel is at positive Y → WRONG.

Same for all wheels:
Right wheels

vis_y = negative
jy    = positive

Left wheels

vis_y = positive
jy    = negative

BRO 😭
Your visual mesh and actual physics joint are on opposite sides.

Gazebo physics uses joint position, not visual mesh.

So plugin thinks:

+Y side = right wheels
-Y side = left wheels

But ROS convention is:

+Y = LEFT
-Y = RIGHT

That explains exactly:

    forward works (because X still okay)

    left/right inverted (because Y mirrored)

FIX THIS

Swap only jy signs.
right_front

Change:

jy=" 0.102054"

to

jy="-0.102054"

right_back

Change:

jy=" 0.102054"

to

jy="-0.102054"

left_front

Change:

jy="-0.102054"

to

jy="0.102054"

left_back

Change:

jy="-0.102054"

to

jy="0.102054"

Issue 2: Your X positions also look flipped

Example:
right_front visual

vis_x="0.083355"

(front)

But joint:

jx="-0.083355"

(back)

BRO SAME PROBLEM IN X TOO.

Visual says front, joint says back.

That means all 4 joints are mirrored in both X and Y relative to visuals.

Example:
Wheel	Visual	Joint
right_front	(+x, -y)	(-x, +y)
left_front	(+x, +y)	(-x, -y)

That is literally 180° mirrored physics layout.
My conclusion

This line from earlier was correct:

    “wheel positions are perfect because exported from Fusion”

Actually… visuals are perfect, but joint origins are not.

You accidentally negated joint coordinates.
Best fix (clean)

For each wheel, make joint origin match visual position pattern:

right_front  -> (+x, -y)
right_back   -> (-x, -y)
left_front   -> (+x, +y)
left_back    -> (-x, +y)

Right now yours is opposite.

Can you try this for just one wheel first?

Change right_front joint from:

<origin xyz="-0.083355 0.102054 0.0439222"/>

to:

<origin xyz="0.083355 -0.102054 0.0439222"/>

Then tell me if wireframe collision jumps to opposite corner in Gazebo.
I’m honestly 99% sure this is the root cause.

